    <Content contentid="1040" contenttypeid="SPA" desc="Spa">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 On call for our guests is a team of well-trained massage and spa therapists who can provide various treatments on guest account within the comfort and privacy of Villa Voyage &ndash; in the shade of the pergola, by the pool, on the balcony or in the cool of the bedroom. Here&rsquo;s a sample of what you&rsquo;ll find on the menu:</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Balinese massage]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 Just the ticket for releasing tension accumulated before the vacation, Balinese massage incorporates gentle stretches, skin rolling and percussion strokes &ndash; techniques passed down through many generations &ndash; to stimulate the flow of oxygen and induce a profound state of relaxation.</p>
]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Fresh seaweed scrub]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 Enjoy a 45-minute massage followed by a natural body scrub made from fresh local seaweed, Aloe Vera and sea salt to remove dead skin, then sink into a warm bath strewn with flowers. You&rsquo;ll emerge rejuvenated, rehydrated and glowing with health, ready to be served a cup of ginger tea.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Manicure and pedicure]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 A flash of pink or crimson on well-groomed nails after a feel-good mani-pedi is the perfect foil for a tropical tan.</p>
]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Papaya body mask]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 After a 45-minute traditional massage, you&rsquo;ll be slathered with a body mask made of fresh papaya and peppermint oil then wrapped in a blanket and left to rest for a while. The treatment finished with a warm bath scented with flowers. This is a great treatment to calm sunburnt skin.</p>
]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="108" contenttypeid="BDR" desc="Bed Rooms">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p> Villa Voyage’s five spacious bedroom suites are equipped with 2 king and 3 queen-size beds, ensuite bathrooms and either balconies or garden terraces.&nbsp; King Koil goose down pillows, deep foam mattresses and designer bed linen ensure a good night’s sleep – with rooms offering the choice of air-conditioning or overhead fan.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Voyage – mezzanine ocean suite]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 Each of the two identical and enormous mezzanine ocean suites expresses the villa&rsquo;s luxury tented safari theme to perfection; a queen-size bed is cocooned under a floating canvas tent suspended from the apex of the alang-alang roof, and the rooms are furnished with wardrobe &lsquo;tents&rsquo; in the dressing area, a folding writing desk, day bed, and steamer trunks. Coconut-wood walls and floors continue the rustic&ndash;luxe look, and large Pucci print cushions add a dash of blue to the otherwise neutral palette of browns and creams. A soaring triangular wall of glass to the front opens onto a large private ironwood balcony furnished with a round table and chairs and a pair of sun loungers and stunning sea views. To the rear of the bedroom, cunningly concealed behind screens of canvas, is a large open-plan bathroom with double basins and mirrors and glazed terrazzo enclosure with rain shower.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images>
            <Image>
              <Caption><![CDATA[Voyage – mezzanine ocean suite]]></Caption>
              <ThumbSizeUrl><![CDATA[/wp-content/themes/voyage/gallery/thumbs/thumbs_voyage-right-side-mezzanine-ocean-suite.jpg]]></ThumbSizeUrl>
              <FullSizeUrl><![CDATA[/wp-content/themes/voyage/gallery/voyage-right-side-mezzanine-ocean-suite.jpg]]></FullSizeUrl>
            </Image>
          </Images>
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Voyage – master suite]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 Below, the master suite continues the &lsquo;luxury under canvas&rsquo; theme, with a four-poster queen bed bedecked with canvas and leather trim, a steamer trunk acting as a media cabinet for the flat-screen 40-inch TV, a canvas seating area that conceals a spare bed, and canvas-backed directors chairs set before sliding doors delightfully opening onto the pool deck. Beyond the bedroom is a dressing area lined with leather-trimmed rattan clothes storage and shelving designed to accommodate the most profligate packer. This leads into the bathroom with double basins, patio with open-air shower and, taking pride of place before sliding doors to the beachside deck, a sculptured terrazzo bathtub.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images>
            <Image>
              <Caption><![CDATA[Voyage – master suite]]></Caption>
              <ThumbSizeUrl><![CDATA[/wp-content/themes/voyage/gallery/thumbs/thumbs_voyage-master-bedroom.jpg]]></ThumbSizeUrl>
              <FullSizeUrl><![CDATA[/wp-content/themes/voyage/gallery/voyage-master-bedroom.jpg]]></FullSizeUrl>
            </Image>
          </Images>
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Voyage – garden suite]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 Next door, facing away from the sea, is the garden suite. The contemporary four-poster bed laden with colourful cushions faces a small courtyard and, on one side, a balcony with table and chairs. A particular feature is the traditional leather travelling desk which doubles as a dressing table. The large ensuite bathroom has a wardrobe of rattan and leather, double basins and, set in a sun-filled patio, an open-air shower.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images>
            <Image>
              <Caption><![CDATA[Voyage – garden suite]]></Caption>
              <ThumbSizeUrl><![CDATA[/wp-content/themes/voyage/gallery/thumbs/thumbs_voyage-kamils-bedroom.jpg]]></ThumbSizeUrl>
              <FullSizeUrl><![CDATA[/wp-content/themes/voyage/gallery/voyage-kamils-bedroom.jpg]]></FullSizeUrl>
            </Image>
          </Images>
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Voyage – garden pavilion suite]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 The garden pavilion suite stands alone, surrounded by white sand in the villa grounds. Its&rsquo; harem-style silken ceiling calls to mind Bedouin tents and desert hospitality, and such romance continues in the soft furnishings and decorations. Walls of glass offer glimpses of the sea and lead onto a private deck. The ensuite bathroom is discreetly tucked around the corner of the walled garden deck.</p>
]]></Description>
          <Images>
            <Image>
              <Caption><![CDATA[Voyage – garden pavilion suite]]></Caption>
